  "prompt": "How do I send gif in whatsapp?",
  "response": "Sending GIFs in WhatsApp is easy! Here's a breakdown of how to do it, depending on your device:\n\n**On iPhone (iOS):**\n\n1.  **Open WhatsApp:** Launch the WhatsApp application on your iPhone.\n2.  **Go to the Chat:** Open the conversation with the person or group you want to send the GIF to.\n3.  **Tap the \"+\" (Plus) Icon:** Tap the \"+\" icon located to the left of the message input field.\n4.  **Select \"Photo & Video Library\":** A menu will pop up.  Tap on \"Photo & Video Library\".\n5.  **GIF Button:** Look for a GIF button at the bottom left corner of your screen. It usually says \"GIF\" in a small box. Tap this button.\n6.  **Browse or Search for a GIF:**\n    *   **Browse:** You'll see a selection of trending GIFs.  Swipe left and right to scroll through different categories.\n    *   **Search:** To find a specific GIF, tap the \"Search\" bar at the bottom of the screen. Type keywords related to the GIF you're looking for (e.g., \"happy,\" \"laughing,\" \"cat\").\n7.  **Select the GIF:** Once you find the GIF you want, tap on it to select it.\n8.  **Preview (Optional):** You'll see a preview of the GIF. You can add a caption above it if you want.\n9.  **Send:** Tap the send arrow (usually a blue arrow pointing upwards) to send the GIF.\n\n**On Android:**\n\n1.  **Open WhatsApp:** Launch the WhatsApp application on your Android device.\n2.  **Go to the Chat:** Open the conversation with the person or group you want to send the GIF to.\n3.  **Tap the Emoji Icon:** Tap the emoji icon (the smiley face) located to the left of the message input field.\n4.  **GIF Button:**  At the bottom of the emoji keyboard, you should see three icons: a smiley face (for emojis), a GIF icon, and a Sticker icon. Tap the GIF icon.\n5.  **Browse or Search for a GIF:**\n    *   **Browse:** WhatsApp will show you a selection of trending GIFs.\n    *   **Search:** Tap the \"Search GIFs\" bar to search for a specific GIF. Type keywords (e.g., \"dancing,\" \"celebrating,\" \"dog\").\n6.  **Select the GIF:** Tap on the GIF you want to send.\n7.  **Preview (Optional):** You'll see a preview of the GIF. You can add a caption above it if you want.\n8.  **Send:** Tap the send arrow (usually a green arrow pointing to the right) to send the GIF.\n\n**Key Things to Remember:**\n\n*   **Internet Connection:** You need an active internet connection (Wi-Fi or mobile data) to search for and send GIFs.\n*   **GIF Size:** WhatsApp has a size limit for GIFs.  Very large GIFs might not send properly.\n*   **From Your Phone's Gallery (for both Android and iPhone):** If you have a GIF saved to your phone's gallery, you can send it like you would send a photo. Just select the GIF from your gallery when choosing to send a photo/video. The difference is WhatsApp will typically ask if you want to send it as a GIF (which preserves the animation) or as a video (which might compress it).\n\n**Troubleshooting:**\n\n*   **GIF Button Missing:** If you don't see the GIF button, make sure your WhatsApp app is up to date. Go to the App Store (iPhone) or Google Play Store (Android) and check for updates.\n*   **GIFs Not Sending:** This could be due to a poor internet connection or a very large GIF file. Try again later with a stronger connection or choose a smaller GIF.\n*   **GIFs are Static:** If the GIF isn't animating when you send it, make sure you're sending it as a GIF and not as a photo.  When selecting from your gallery, WhatsApp usually gives you the option.\n\nThat covers the basics! Enjoy sending GIFs on WhatsApp.\n",
